d Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1290–1345":"1290–1345","1292–Female":"1292–Deceased","1327–1365":"1327–1365","1252–Male":"1252–Deceased","1248–1291":"1248–1291","1327":"1327","1248":"1248","1345":"1345","1365":"1365","1252":"1252","1292":"1292","1291":"1291","1290":"1290","Abt 1327":"about 1327","Lovat Castle, Beauly, Inverness-Shire, Scotland":"Beauly, Inverness-shire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Inverness,Inverness,Scotland":"Inverness, Inverness-shire, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bisset","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish (of Norman origin): variant of   Bissett  .","French: from a diminutive of Old French <i>bisse</i> ‘fine linen’ (see   Bisson  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Bissett","meanings":["Scottish (of Norman origin): nickname from Old French <i>biset</i> ‘dark’, a diminutive of <i>bis</i> (see   Biss  ).","Altered form of French <b>Bizet</b>: nickname for someone with a dark complexion, derived from <i>bis</i> ‘grayish-brown’. Altered ending reflects the Canadian and American French practice of sounding the final <i>-t</i>. Compare   Bissette  .","History: The surname <i>Bissett</i> (see 1 above) was brought to Scotland from Nottinghamshire <i>c.</i> 1175 by Henricus Byset, an Englishman who became a retainer of King William the Lion. — It was Jean George Bizet from Haute-Saône, France, whose surname was changed to <i>Bissett</i> (see 2 above) after his immigration to NS, Canada, in 1752."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Bisset was born in 1290, in Inverness, Inverness-shire, Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, Thomas Bisset, was 38 and his mother, Mary Oliver, was 42. He had at least 1 son with Anne Bradburn. He died in 1345, at the age of 55."},"et":{"1290–1345":"1290–1345","1292–Female":"1292–Surnud","1327–1365":"1327–1365","1252–Male":"1252–Surnud","1248–1291":"1248–1291","1327":"1327","1248":"1248","1345":"1345","1365":"1365","1252":"1252","1292":"1292","1291":"1291","1290":"1290","Abt 1327":"umbes 1327","Lovat Castle, Beauly, Inverness-Shire, Scotland":"Beauly, Inverness-shire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Inverness,Inverness,Scotland":"Inverness, Inverness-shire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1290–1345":"1290–1345","1292–Female":"1292–Kuollut","1327–1365":"1327–1365","1252–Male":"1252–Kuollut","1248–1291":"1248–1291","1327":"1327","1248":"1248","1345":"1345","1365":"1365","1252":"1252","1292":"1292","1291":"1291","1290":"1290","Abt 1327":"noin 1327","Lovat Castle, Beauly, Inverness-Shire, Scotland":"Beauly, Inverness-shire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Inverness,Inverness,Scotland":"Inverness, Inverness-shire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1290–1345":"1290–1345","1292–Female":"1292–Décédée","1327–1365":"1327–1365","1252–Male":"1252–Décédé","1248–1291":"1248–1291","1327":"1327","1248":"1248","1345":"1345","1365":"1365","1252":"1252","1292":"1292","1291":"1291","1290":"1290","Abt 1327":"environ 1327","Lovat Castle, Beauly, Inverness-Shire, Scotland":"Beauly, Inverness-shire, Écosse","Scotland":"Écosse","Inverness,Inverness,Scotland":"Inverness, Inverness-shire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Thomas Bisset est né en 1290, à Inverness, Inverness-shire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni, son père, Thomas Bisset, avait 38 ans et sa mère, Mary Oliver, avait 42 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Anne Bradburn. Il est décédé en 1345, à l’âge de 55 ans."},"de":{"1290–1345":"12